So I’ll tell this as a story: When kickoff happened, my team as well as many others, wanted to get our hands on some balls before they were all sold out. The only way we could get the discount off of andymark was buying 24+ of the same color. So naturally we thought “lets just buy 24 and sell them out to other teams in the area/exchange for blues”. It did not go as well as we planned and we’ve only been able to acquire 3 blue balls. Fast forward to today and our programmers are having trouble making an AI since they can’t take pictures fast enough, so the though was this:
What if we asked CD to send some pictures of blue balls so that everyone in a similar situation has the ability to train an AI with both colors?

1000+ images of 2022's game balls for vision Technical
Good day, Our team labeled 1000+ images of the new game ball (blue and red). We ended up not needing it, but if your team would like to use it, you can download the collection (1 GB) below. https://drive.google.com/file/d/1F-qmSxL0R-z7l7R3ozSfZic0yWLF9QCw/view?usp=sharing Class names: [redball, blueball] Images: 1000+ Label-type: rectangle Hope this helps! Jack Programming Lead - Texas Torque (FRC 1477)
